Is it important to distinguish the 0 values from the positive ones when comparing the signs?
If not, maybe we can simplify a bit:
```C++
    // Compute and compare signs.
    int sign_a = (a1 < 0) ^ (a2 < 0) ? -1 : 1;
    int sign_b = (b1 < 0) ^ (b2 < 0) ? -1 : 1;
    if (sign_a != sign_b) return sign_a <=> sign_b;

    auto result = Abs256(a1) * Abs256(a2) <=> Abs256(b1) * Abs256(b2);
    return (sign_a >= 0) ? result : 0 <=> result;

